  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense in most jurisdictions around the world. It is typically addressed under criminal legislation and financial crime statutes. Money laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Most countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws that criminalize such activities, with potential penalties including fines and imprisonment.",
